figure out what the users, movies and actors tables look like

Ruby on Rails
-------------
imdb
	users

	id (primary key) | username | hashed password | Date of Birth | favorite movies (foreign key) | favorite actors (foreign key)
	-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ex:  1               | user1234 | *************** | May 1st 1994  | 19, 55, 90, 45                | 87, 47, 23, 55	
	
	movies

	id (primary key) | rating | title | genre      
    -----------------------------------------

	actors

	id (primary key) | name | movie_id (foreign key)
	------------------------------------------------

	movie_reviews

	id (primary key) | movie_id (foreign key) | user_id (foreign key)| review
	------------------------------------------------------------------------

	actor reviews

	id (primary key) | actor_id (foreign key) | user_id (foreign key) | review
